<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5842> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5842" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Probably a Legate in Africa under Caesar, for whom he defended Achulla (Bell. Afr. 33; 43)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5260> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5260" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Though appointed a Legate of Caesar on the recommendation of Appius Claudius, he was returned to Rome for trial by edict of the Praetor P. Servilius (Cic. Att. 4.15.9)." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5186> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5186" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Celebrated the Floralia as Aedile (Val. Max. 7.10.8; cf. Bell. Afr. 33.2; Dio 39.32.2; and on his trial in 54, Cic. Att. 4.15.9; Senec. Rhet. Contr. 7.4.8). See 69, Aediles of the Plebs, on Cicero." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/5088> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #5088" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Presented a bill for Cicero's recall at the beginning of his tribunate (Cic. P. Red. in Sen. 21; cf. Dom. 70; Sed. 72); and in September proposed a bill to give Pompey charge of the grain supply which exceeded the consular one (see above) in the grant of financial powers and of the maim imperium (Cic. Att. 4.1.7)." .
